<TITLE> More BTTB graft unearthed, Tk 52 crore worth </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 19 (bdnews24.com)  The Anticorruption Commission has unearthed corruption amounting to Tk 52 crore at two revenue offices of the former BTTB (now BTCL), said a top ACC official on Monday. "The commission will send notices to those under investigation, demanding their wealth statements," said ACC director general (administration) Colonel Hanif Iqbal Monday. "Divisional cases will also be lodged." "The BTCL collects revenue through two offices. Fom 2000-2001 to 2007-2008, misappropriation of Tk 16.38 crore been unearthed at revenue office-1," he said. "In revenue office-2 Tk 36.17 was found missing." "The money was misappropriated mostly through issue of fake bills and vouchers," said the director general. bdnew
